ðŸ“œ Common Jenkins CLI Commands

| Command                  | Description                                 |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |
| `list-jobs`              | Lists all jobs in Jenkins                   |
| `build <job-name>`       | Triggers a build for the specified job      |
| `console <job-name>`     | Displays console output of the latest build |
| `get-job <job-name>`     | Downloads job configuration (XML)           |
| `update-job <job-name>`  | Updates job config from XML input           |
| `create-job <job-name>`  | Creates a job using an XML config           |
| `delete-job <job-name>`  | Deletes a job                               |
| `disable-job <job-name>` | Disables a job                              |
| `enable-job <job-name>`  | Enables a disabled job                      |
| `who-am-i`               | Shows authenticated user                    |
| `version`                | Displays Jenkins version                    |
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Shell commands for jenkins service:

# Start Jenkins
sudo systemctl start jenkins

# Stop Jenkins
sudo systemctl stop jenkins

# Restart Jenkins
sudo systemctl restart jenkins

# Check Jenkins status
sudo systemctl status jenkins

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Before running CLI commands, download the Jenkins CLI jar:

wget http://your-jenkins-url/jnlpJars/jenkins-cli.jar

ðŸŸ¢ Basic CLI Usage:
java -jar jenkins-cli.jar -s http://your-jenkins-url/ command [options]





